                        <summary>What happens if I refuse the breath test?</summary>
                        <p>If you refuse a breathalyzer or blood test, you'll face <strong>automatic penalties under Michigan's Implied Consent Law</strong>:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>1-year driver's license suspension</strong> (separate from any criminal penalties)</li>
                            <li><strong>6 points on your driving record</strong></li>
                            <li>Your refusal can be used as <strong>evidence of guilt</strong> in court ("Why refuse unless you knew you were drunk?")</li>
                            <li>Police can still obtain a warrant to forcibly draw your blood</li>
                        </ul>
