                        <p><strong>Not necessarily.</strong> While Super Drunk allows up to 180 days in jail, most first-time offenders receive:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Probation</strong> (12-24 months)</li>
                            <li><strong>Community service</strong> (40-360 hours)</li>
                            <li><strong>Substance abuse treatment or counseling</strong></li>
                            <li><strong>Fines and court costs</strong></li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Jail time is more likely if:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Your BAC was extremely high (0.25%+)</li>
                            <li>You caused an accident or injury</li>
                            <li>You have prior OWI convictions</li>
                            <li>You violated probation or bond conditions</li>
                        </ul>
